### VIM ########################################################################

1. Ctrl + Enter:  Creates \n between {} like in Eclipse, nice for methods
2. '.       : jump to last modification line (SUPER)
3. save Markers mx (set marker at current position with letter x)
4. go to Marker 'x (go to marker saved under letter x)
5. H, M, L to jump to High (top of) the screen Middle, and Low (bottom) of the screen.
6. Use { and } to jump over blocks of text, ( and ) to jump between sentences.
7. Use [[ and ]] to jump between function.
8. Use TX or tX to move before the prev or next char X

### PLUGINS 
# you complete me
1. <Ctrl + y> to accept a selection

### VIM SPELL CHECKER
http://tips.webdesign10.com/vim/how-use-vims-spellchecker

# To activate / deactivate
1. :set spell                  
2. :set nospell               

#When in spell checking mode:
z=   to show suggestions
zg   add word to dictionary 
zug  undo addition of word
]s   next misspelled element 
[s   previous misspelled element


################################################################################

### ZSH ########################################################################

NOTE can replace command (e.g. ls) with other commands such as rm

1. ls **/*.c  : use ** as wild card to descend into directories.
2. ls *.(c|h) : use *.(arg1|arg2...) to search with either .arg1 or .arg2 ending
3. Use tab autocompletion with EVERYTHING! (e.g. kill process, etc)

