                                  - - - - - - - –
                                  |     Bash     |
                                  - - - - - - - –
1. csv_join.in is a simple line, which line by line contains the input for said program
   > /dev/null will redirec the stdout of the output of the program to null which is 
   like a black hole.
                        ./a.out < csv_join.in > /dev/null

2. Searching:

    find . -name "*.java" | xargs grep "pattern"

    find will first filter all files in current folder ( . ), with given pattern
    "*.java", | operator is a pipe, so the filtered files will be piped to the right,
    which are then passed as arguments to xargs, xargs is like a map in scala, for each 
    element in the list it will apply the command (in this case grep "pattern", which
    looks for said pattern).


